                            <comment id="20406" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 Sep 2011 14:57:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; 06:21:51:LDISKFS-fs warning (device dm-0): ldiskfs_fill_super: extents feature not enabled on this filesystem, use tune2fs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FYI, this message is a complete red herring for the MDT (i.e. unrelated to this or any problem, in case there was any uncertainty), and we should remove it from our ldiskfs filesystems.  I don&apos;t think that extents on the MDT can possibly help, and will likely hurt performance since directory blocks are allocated one-at-a-time and storing them as extents is less efficient.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
